*Reading*

People in DH: There is a rich critical discourse, the subject of the many excellent digital scholars talks in the past year, around race, gender, and (for lack of a better way of putting it) people in DH. This is just a sampling and starting points (feel free to add more suggestions).

http://dhdebates.gc.cuny.edu/debates/text/97 (Links to an external site.)

http://dhdebates.gc.cuny.edu/debates/text/72 (Links to an external site.)

http://journalofdigitalhumanities.org/1-1/all-the-digital-humanists-are-white-all-the-nerds-are-men-but-some-of-us-are-brave-by-moya-z-bailey/ (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.

http://dhdebates.gc.cuny.edu/debates/text/29 (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.

http://miriamposner.com/blog/some-things-to-think-about-before-you-exhort-everyone-to-code/  (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.http://infolet.it/2015/07/12/monocultural-humanities/ (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.

